00:00:00,040 --> 00:00:14,740
( Watch on Kissasia.vip )

1
00:01:00,100 --> 00:01:02,900
=Daughter of Fortune=

2
00:01:02,900 --> 00:01:05,460
(Adapted from the novel
"Phoenix Palace Dream" by Lan Jiujiu)

3
00:01:05,485 --> 00:01:08,405
=Episode 15=

4
00:01:26,359 --> 00:01:26,920
Lady Shen.

5
00:01:30,280 --> 00:01:31,079
Lord Jiang.

6
00:01:31,879 --> 00:01:33,079
I didn't expect His Majesty

7
00:01:33,480 --> 00:01:35,239
would allow you
to enter Library Pavilion.

8
00:01:35,310 --> 00:01:37,550
His Majesty asked me to attend
the Xunlu Poetry Gathering.

9
00:01:37,560 --> 00:01:39,799
I came to look through past poems.

10
00:01:41,120 --> 00:01:42,719
It seems His Majesty is fond of you.

11
00:01:46,799 --> 00:01:49,200
You grew up with His Majesty.

12
00:01:49,519 --> 00:01:51,560
I suppose you understand him well.

13
00:01:54,439 --> 00:01:55,879
If you spend more time with him,

14
00:01:56,319 --> 00:01:57,319
you'll know him too.

15
00:01:58,519 --> 00:01:59,760
He doesn't feel secure easily,

16
00:02:00,000 --> 00:02:01,439
and he doesn't trust people quickly.

17
00:02:02,359 --> 00:02:04,319
You'll inevitably be treated coldly
at times

18
00:02:04,400 --> 00:02:05,640
when serving by his side.

19
00:02:06,879 --> 00:02:08,120
But once he trusts you,

20
00:02:08,400 --> 00:02:09,680
he treats you very well.

21
00:02:10,560 --> 00:02:11,800
Besides, I think...

22
00:02:14,719 --> 00:02:15,520
What is it?

23
00:02:18,000 --> 00:02:20,520
His Majesty was willing
to set aside his pride at Jinsong House

24
00:02:20,800 --> 00:02:21,790
and kneel to pour liquor.

25
00:02:22,560 --> 00:02:24,719
He doesn't just like you,

26
00:02:24,840 --> 00:02:25,680
he trusts you too.

27
00:02:27,360 --> 00:02:29,439
Please don't take
what happened at Jinsong House

28
00:02:29,439 --> 00:02:30,319
to heart.

29
00:02:30,719 --> 00:02:32,159
I never meant to offend you.

30
00:02:34,639 --> 00:02:35,439
I know.

31
00:02:38,560 --> 00:02:39,879
I happened to be looking through

32
00:02:39,879 --> 00:02:40,990
the records from the past
Xunlu Poetry Gatherings.

33
00:02:41,000 --> 00:02:42,560
(Rules of the Xunlu Poetry Gathering)
These are the rules. You can have a look.

34
00:02:42,960 --> 00:02:46,120
On the day of the gathering,
I'll accompany you there.

35
00:02:48,680 --> 00:02:51,039
Why are you treating me
with such kindness?

36
00:02:52,560 --> 00:02:53,560
I want him to be happy.

37
00:02:56,000 --> 00:02:57,990
When we were children,
I pitied him for being weak

38
00:02:58,000 --> 00:02:59,500
and admired him for enduring so much.

39
00:03:00,159 --> 00:03:01,630
I treated him like a younger brother.

40
00:03:02,360 --> 00:03:04,560
Later, I admired
his courage and ambition

41
00:03:05,000 --> 00:03:06,660
as he dared to fight
against fate itself,

42
00:03:07,000 --> 00:03:08,830
and I came to see him
as the ruler of Daliang.

43
00:03:12,039 --> 00:03:13,159
People are always like this.

44
00:03:13,599 --> 00:03:14,479
They place their hopes

45
00:03:14,479 --> 00:03:16,479
in someone stronger than themselves.

46
00:03:17,199 --> 00:03:18,439
They hope someone else can do

47
00:03:18,680 --> 00:03:20,319
what they cannot accomplish for them.

48
00:03:22,599 --> 00:03:24,719
Lord Jiang, you're a frank man.

49
00:03:27,700 --> 00:03:29,700
Let me explain to you how things work
in the Xunlu Pavilion.

50
00:03:31,360 --> 00:03:31,919
Alright.

51
00:03:35,039 --> 00:03:36,919
I didn't know there were so many rules.

52
00:03:37,319 --> 00:03:39,639
His Majesty didn't mention any of this.

53
00:03:40,080 --> 00:03:41,240
That's just how he is.

54
00:03:41,660 --> 00:03:42,719
Please be patient with him.

55
00:03:44,800 --> 00:03:45,560
If only His Majesty

56
00:03:45,560 --> 00:03:47,680
had half of your good temper.

57
00:03:48,000 --> 00:03:48,990
Greetings, Your Majesty.

58
00:03:49,400 --> 00:03:49,800
Mm.

59
00:03:53,919 --> 00:03:54,800
Your Majesty.

60
00:03:55,199 --> 00:03:55,719
Mm.

61
00:03:56,199 --> 00:03:57,319
I shall take my leave now.

62
00:03:57,759 --> 00:03:58,680
Why the hurry?

63
00:03:58,700 --> 00:04:00,770
You're making it seem like
I'm disturbing the two of you.

64
00:04:03,280 --> 00:04:04,719
We shall play a game, Official Jiang.

65
00:04:05,120 --> 00:04:05,800
Sit.

66
00:04:06,600 --> 00:04:07,360
Yes, Your Majesty.

67
00:04:12,439 --> 00:04:13,680
Are you expecting me

68
00:04:13,800 --> 00:04:15,630
to serve the two of you
while you play weiqi?

69
00:04:20,330 --> 00:04:21,860
- Please, Your Majesty.
- Please, Your Majesty.

70
00:04:22,680 --> 00:04:24,160
I had no idea

71
00:04:24,439 --> 00:04:26,279
you two were so in sync.

72
00:04:37,720 --> 00:04:39,290
Your Majesty, you can't place it there.

73
00:04:40,800 --> 00:04:41,990
A true gentleman doesn't speak

74
00:04:42,199 --> 00:04:43,240
while watching a game.

75
00:04:50,279 --> 00:04:52,480
That was a terrible move.

76
00:04:53,279 --> 00:04:54,199
You do it then.

77
00:04:56,160 --> 00:04:57,720
I'll do it.

78
00:05:05,439 --> 00:05:06,560
See, Your Majesty?

79
00:05:06,839 --> 00:05:08,000
That's how weiqi is played.

80
00:05:08,290 --> 00:05:10,079
What you were doing earlier
was utter chaos.

81
00:05:10,560 --> 00:05:11,639
Playing weiqi

82
00:05:12,399 --> 00:05:13,879
is much like governing a state.

83
00:05:14,040 --> 00:05:15,319
Only through great chaos

84
00:05:16,319 --> 00:05:18,079
can true order arise.

85
00:05:20,519 --> 00:05:22,079
(Of all places,)

86
00:05:22,439 --> 00:05:24,319
(he picked the only losing move.)

87
00:05:24,800 --> 00:05:26,600
(Do you really not know how to play?)

88
00:05:26,600 --> 00:05:28,690
Your skill has improved greatly indeed,
Your Majesty.

89
00:05:30,439 --> 00:05:31,480
Let's go.

90
00:05:35,160 --> 00:05:37,040
Attend the Xunlu Poetry Gathering.

91
00:05:38,360 --> 00:05:39,000
Yes.

92
00:05:51,560 --> 00:05:52,600
I'll return first.

93
00:05:52,920 --> 00:05:54,000
Rest well.

94
00:05:54,240 --> 00:05:55,480
Won't you stay a little longer?

95
00:05:56,240 --> 00:05:57,439
I have memorials to review.

96
00:05:58,040 --> 00:05:58,759
Your Majesty,

97
00:06:00,240 --> 00:06:02,279
I reviewed the game of weiqi
from earlier

98
00:06:02,600 --> 00:06:05,040
and realized
you intentionally let Lord Jiang win.

99
00:06:06,279 --> 00:06:08,519
Should I not

100
00:06:08,759 --> 00:06:09,879
have beaten him earlier?

101
00:06:13,439 --> 00:06:14,639
I can't beat him.

102
00:06:15,070 --> 00:06:16,040
You may do as you please.

103
00:06:17,750 --> 00:06:19,040
I bid farewell to Your Majesty.

104
00:06:21,480 --> 00:06:24,120
To think His Majesty
would intentionally lose to Lord Jiang.

105
00:06:25,759 --> 00:06:27,879
Those two were quite interesting.

106
00:06:40,800 --> 00:06:42,040
These flowers are beautiful.

107
00:06:45,240 --> 00:06:47,920
Why are you still in the palace so late?

108
00:06:48,279 --> 00:06:49,560
I went to the Library Pavilion

109
00:06:50,240 --> 00:06:51,480
and happened to play a game

110
00:06:52,279 --> 00:06:53,560
with Lady Shen.

111
00:07:03,199 --> 00:07:04,920
Are you close with Shen Zhinian?

112
00:07:06,519 --> 00:07:07,480
We met a few times.

113
00:07:08,879 --> 00:07:10,120
What kind of person

114
00:07:10,519 --> 00:07:11,759
do you think she is?

115
00:07:14,680 --> 00:07:15,759
She's beautiful

116
00:07:16,879 --> 00:07:17,839
and somewhat talented.

117
00:07:18,519 --> 00:07:19,439
That's all?

118
00:07:21,639 --> 00:07:22,879
Then why does His Majesty

119
00:07:23,000 --> 00:07:24,040
like her so much?

120
00:07:24,360 --> 00:07:25,399
Don't overthink.

121
00:07:25,959 --> 00:07:26,959
Focus on recovering.

122
00:07:28,360 --> 00:07:29,920
Do you like her too?

123
00:07:30,360 --> 00:07:31,920
You were speaking up for her.

124
00:07:33,040 --> 00:07:35,240
You even played weiqi with her.

125
00:07:35,300 --> 00:07:37,500
I just happened to run into her
at the Library Pavilion.

126
00:07:38,210 --> 00:07:40,490
His Majesty sent her to attend
the Xunlu Poetry Gathering,

127
00:07:40,839 --> 00:07:42,120
so she asked me a few questions.

128
00:07:45,500 --> 00:07:47,319
That poetry gathering was founded
by Dowager Consort Qin

129
00:07:47,319 --> 00:07:48,879
in her younger days.

130
00:07:50,480 --> 00:07:52,360
He never took me there.

131
00:07:54,439 --> 00:07:57,000
Does His Majesty like her that much?

132
00:07:59,519 --> 00:08:00,720
You shouldn't dwell on these.

133
00:08:01,959 --> 00:08:02,959
Get well soon.

134
00:08:05,439 --> 00:08:07,399
You're just like Father.

135
00:08:08,360 --> 00:08:09,879
You're heartless.

136
00:08:11,319 --> 00:08:13,120
At least His Majesty won't upset me.

137
00:08:14,879 --> 00:08:16,639
You two are worse than he is.

138
00:08:18,160 --> 00:08:20,879
Eunuch Pan,
help Her Highness back to rest.

139
00:08:22,399 --> 00:08:24,639
Your Highness, Lord Jiang is busy
with official duties.

140
00:08:24,839 --> 00:08:25,680
Let him return.

141
00:08:26,800 --> 00:08:27,680
I take my leave.

142
00:08:33,840 --> 00:08:35,600
Who knows whether he's busy with work

143
00:08:36,120 --> 00:08:37,799
or busy because of Shen Zhinian?

144
00:08:44,559 --> 00:08:46,960
Didn't you say
you wouldn't interfere in the game?

145
00:08:47,679 --> 00:08:50,200
I had intended
to remain behind the scenes

146
00:08:50,600 --> 00:08:52,679
and watch them destroy each other.

147
00:08:53,000 --> 00:08:55,159
But a new piece suddenly appeared
on the board.

148
00:08:55,960 --> 00:08:57,240
If I don't act now,

149
00:08:57,639 --> 00:08:59,320
it may fall into someone else's hands.

150
00:09:00,080 --> 00:09:02,390
You always say weiqi must be played
with patience and caution.

151
00:09:03,039 --> 00:09:05,840
Isn't entering the game now too risky?

152
00:09:07,480 --> 00:09:08,320
You're mistaken.

153
00:09:09,279 --> 00:09:10,720
I'm not a player in this game.

154
00:09:11,480 --> 00:09:12,759
I'm the one manipulating it.

155
00:09:13,440 --> 00:09:14,879
They may know how to fight and kill,

156
00:09:15,000 --> 00:09:17,400
but they don't understand
that a move must be laid out in advance.

157
00:09:17,720 --> 00:09:19,399
That's why they're bound to lose.

158
00:09:23,799 --> 00:09:26,399
(Xunlu Pavilion)
Third round, Lin Qing of Jin won.

159
00:09:26,559 --> 00:09:27,799
You dare challenge me?

160
00:09:28,000 --> 00:09:28,639
Get lost.

161
00:09:32,240 --> 00:09:32,960
Who else

162
00:09:33,080 --> 00:09:34,879
dares step forward?

163
00:09:36,000 --> 00:09:37,320
Just let him have the win already.

164
00:09:37,320 --> 00:09:37,919
Why should we?

165
00:09:37,919 --> 00:09:38,440
Right?

166
00:09:38,440 --> 00:09:39,000
Exactly.

167
00:09:41,120 --> 00:09:42,120
I'll challenge you.

168
00:09:43,159 --> 00:09:45,120
Has Daliang run out of talent?

169
00:09:45,279 --> 00:09:47,240
Sending a woman to compete instead?

170
00:09:47,240 --> 00:09:48,399
If I dare step forward,

171
00:09:48,570 --> 00:09:50,559
why would you fear
accepting the challenge, sir?

172
00:09:50,919 --> 00:09:51,600
Miss,

173
00:09:51,759 --> 00:09:52,960
don't cry after you lose.

174
00:09:54,000 --> 00:09:55,600
That young lady certainly has  courage.

175
00:09:55,600 --> 00:09:56,919
(Deek Hunt Poetry Gathering)

176
00:09:56,919 --> 00:09:58,279
Can she do it?

177
00:10:00,440 --> 00:10:01,639
She must have confidence.

178
00:10:01,879 --> 00:10:05,000
(All those poems
were written by me in my previous life)

179
00:10:05,000 --> 00:10:07,360
(to help Lu Jianglin win first place.)

180
00:10:07,919 --> 00:10:09,200
(No wonder he kept winning.)

181
00:10:10,000 --> 00:10:11,120
(Looks like Shen Nanqiao)

182
00:10:11,120 --> 00:10:13,600
(memorized my poems from my past life
and gave them to him.)

183
00:10:18,639 --> 00:10:19,200
What?

184
00:10:19,639 --> 00:10:20,440
Afraid now?

185
00:10:20,450 --> 00:10:21,500
I'll take your challenge.

186
00:10:21,559 --> 00:10:23,480
But if you lose,

187
00:10:23,679 --> 00:10:25,240
you must kneel and serve tea in apology

188
00:10:25,840 --> 00:10:27,639
to the master of Xunlu Pavilion.

189
00:10:28,080 --> 00:10:29,279
Me, lose?

190
00:10:30,400 --> 00:10:31,390
That would never happen.

191
00:10:31,840 --> 00:10:32,799
Absolutely impossible.

192
00:10:37,120 --> 00:10:37,840
Let's begin.

193
00:10:38,039 --> 00:10:38,639
What's this?

194
00:10:39,039 --> 00:10:40,639
Do you need to stare at my handsome face

195
00:10:41,120 --> 00:10:42,279
before you can write?

196
00:10:42,639 --> 00:10:43,559
The closer I stand,

197
00:10:43,879 --> 00:10:45,159
the better I can admire

198
00:10:45,159 --> 00:10:47,879
your expression after you lose.

199
00:10:48,480 --> 00:10:49,759
You're certainly confident.

200
00:10:49,840 --> 00:10:50,759
Very well.

201
00:10:51,360 --> 00:10:52,519
Today, I'll teach you

202
00:10:53,039 --> 00:10:55,799
how a gentle lady should behave.

203
00:11:04,919 --> 00:11:08,279
(Deep in the valley grow orchids,
their green leaves perfectly poised.)

204
00:11:09,679 --> 00:11:11,799
(Their faint fragrance)

205
00:11:12,500 --> 00:11:13,960
(drifts beyond the doors of clouds.)

206
00:11:21,200 --> 00:11:24,039
(If the peony understood
the grace of noble solitude,)

207
00:11:24,799 --> 00:11:26,759
(why fear dust and mud)

208
00:11:27,080 --> 00:11:28,600
(sullying its pure white petals?)

209
00:11:30,519 --> 00:11:31,320
I'm done.

210
00:11:35,600 --> 00:11:37,360
(She wrote the exact same poem as I?)

211
00:11:37,840 --> 00:11:38,919
(What's going on?)

212
00:11:39,039 --> 00:11:40,600
How does she know the last two lines?

213
00:11:41,200 --> 00:11:42,960
This is another form of a poetry duel.

214
00:11:43,399 --> 00:11:44,720
You write the first half,

215
00:11:44,860 --> 00:11:46,000
and I answer with the second.

216
00:11:46,480 --> 00:11:47,919
I underestimated you.

217
00:11:51,080 --> 00:11:53,759
(Snow presses upon jade-like boughs,
showing pure hues of elegance.)

218
00:11:54,200 --> 00:11:55,720
(A faint fragrance...)

219
00:11:57,039 --> 00:11:57,960
(What comes next?)

220
00:11:58,200 --> 00:12:00,919
Snow presses upon jade-like boughs,
showing pure hues of elegance.

221
00:12:00,919 --> 00:12:03,180
A faint fragrance drifts softly
through the humble gates.

222
00:12:03,240 --> 00:12:05,080
If all flowers understood
such graceful poise,

223
00:12:05,679 --> 00:12:06,879
why fear frost and bitter winds

224
00:12:08,320 --> 00:12:09,480
that pierce to the bone?

225
00:12:09,519 --> 00:12:10,960
- Excellent!
- Nice poem!

226
00:12:12,039 --> 00:12:13,360
That's brilliant!

227
00:12:14,039 --> 00:12:16,480
Miss, where exactly did
these poems come from?

228
00:12:16,879 --> 00:12:18,120
I wrote them myself.

229
00:12:18,320 --> 00:12:19,039
Impossible.

230
00:12:19,360 --> 00:12:21,000
Would you like to continue, sir?

231
00:12:21,310 --> 00:12:22,780
Daliang only won through petty tricks.

232
00:12:22,800 --> 00:12:23,840
You people don't keep your word.

233
00:12:24,840 --> 00:12:26,200
You've been competing in Daliang

234
00:12:26,200 --> 00:12:27,080
for two days now.

235
00:12:27,200 --> 00:12:29,039
Have you seen any scholar here

236
00:12:29,039 --> 00:12:30,279
refuse to admit defeat?

237
00:12:30,679 --> 00:12:32,120
You simply can't accept losing.

238
00:12:32,120 --> 00:12:33,360
Sore loser!

239
00:12:33,480 --> 00:12:35,000
The people of Jin are unethical.

240
00:12:35,159 --> 00:12:36,279
Shameless!

241
00:12:36,759 --> 00:12:37,399
Fine.

242
00:12:37,919 --> 00:12:38,519
I concede.

243
00:12:48,480 --> 00:12:53,600
♪Broken dreams,
listening to the light rain♪

244
00:12:55,320 --> 00:13:00,560
♪Bitter cold, bringing mist to the eyes♪

245
00:13:02,200 --> 00:13:04,560
♪If we don't meet♪

246
00:13:04,760 --> 00:13:08,000
♪Flowers bloom and fall in shame♪

247
00:13:08,200 --> 00:13:14,720
♪If we meet again,
the peaches will be warm♪

248
00:13:15,080 --> 00:13:21,520
♪Spring breeze passes,
dancing through the years♪

249
00:13:21,880 --> 00:13:28,200
♪Brewing longing,
remembering past lives♪

250
00:13:28,720 --> 00:13:35,400
♪Hard to meet, and just as hard to part♪

251
00:13:35,400 --> 00:13:42,280
♪Who planted the beans
that grew into lotuses?♪

252
00:13:42,520 --> 00:13:48,400
♪Spring breeze passes,
composing the fleeting years♪

253
00:13:49,320 --> 00:13:55,920
♪Clouds on Mount Wu,
no sails on the sea♪

254
00:13:56,080 --> 00:14:02,760
♪Wanting to fold my heart
into a paper kite♪

255
00:14:03,040 --> 00:14:09,480
♪But the ties are too tangled to sever♪

